---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Our Story | WV Wild Outdoors" description="From a small shop on the back roads to a new corner lot. The story of WV Wild Outdoors.">
  <Header />

  <main class="bg-brand-cream">

    <!-- Storybook Container -->
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-20">

      <!-- Title Page -->
      <header class="text-center mb-16 pb-12 border-b-2 border-brand-brown/20">
        <p class="font-hand text-brand-orange text-2xl -rotate-1 mb-4">A West Virginia Story</p>
        <h1 class="font-display font-black text-4xl md:text-6xl text-brand-brown leading-tight mb-6">
          WV Wild Outdoors
        </h1>
        <p class="text-brand-mud/60 font-hand text-xl">Since 2008</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Page 1: The Journey Begins - Bridge -->
      <section class="storybook-page mb-20">
        <div class="storybook-full-bleed -mx-6 md:-mx-12 mb-8">
          <img
            src="/story-bridge-beginning.jpg"
            alt="The bridge on Old Route 19, the road that leads to where it all started"
            class="w-full rounded shadow-2xl"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
          <p class="font-hand text-xl text-brand-mud/50 mb-6">Old Route 19</p>
          <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed">
            This bridge takes you down the back roads to where it all started. Past the hollers, through the hills, into the heart of West Virginia.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Page 2: Finding Home -->
      <section class="storybook-page mb-20 text-center py-8">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
          We live in <strong class="text-brand-brown">Sutton</strong>, our church is down the road in <strong class="text-brand-brown">Tesla</strong>, and in <strong class="text-brand-brown">2013</strong> we settled the business right here in Little Birch.
        </p>
        <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display text-brand-brown mb-4">
          We aren't just a store off the highway.
        </p>
        <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-hand text-brand-orange -rotate-1">
          We are your neighbors.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Page 3: The Little Birch Shop - Old Store Sketch -->
      <section class="storybook-page mb-20">
        <div class="storybook-spread md:flex md:items-center md:gap-10">

          <div class="storybook-image md:w-1/2 mb-8 md:mb-0">
            <img
              src="/story-sketch-old-store.jpg"
              alt="Pencil sketch of the original WV Wild Outdoors store in Little Birch"
              class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-xl"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <p class="text-center font-hand text-brand-mud/50 mt-3">The Little Birch shop</p>
          </div>

          <div class="storybook-text md:w-1/2">
            <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed mb-6">
              <span class="font-display font-bold text-brand-brown text-3xl">W</span>e started back in <strong class="text-brand-brown">2008</strong> out in the New River Gorge area.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Just a sporting goods store for "all sports." We worked hard, but that location... well, we couldn't make it there.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud/80 italic">
              Sometimes the Lord closes a door so you have to move.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Page 4: The Flood - Full Illustration -->
      <section class="storybook-page mb-20">

        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-brand-brown text-center mb-8">
          The Flood
        </h2>

        <div class="storybook-full-bleed -mx-6 md:-mx-12 mb-8">
          <img
            src="/story-sketch-flood.jpg"
            alt="Pencil sketch depicting the June 2016 flood waters devastating the shop"
            class="w-full shadow-2xl"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
          <p class="font-hand text-2xl text-brand-mud/60 mb-4">June 23, 2016</p>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed mb-4">
            A thousand-year storm. Eight inches of rain in twelve hours. The Elk River rose higher than it had since 1888. Twenty-three souls lost across West Virginia.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed">
            The Little Birch shop took on water. Over <strong class="text-brand-brown text-2xl">$70,000</strong> in inventory — gone.
          </p>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Page 5: The Cleanup -->
      <section class="storybook-page mb-20">

        <div class="storybook-full-bleed -mx-6 md:-mx-12 mb-8">
          <img
            src="/story-sketch-cleanup.jpg"
            alt="Pencil sketch showing the lot covered in debris after the flood waters receded"
            class="w-full shadow-2xl"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
          <p class="font-hand text-xl text-brand-mud/50 mb-6">The Aftermath</p>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed mb-6">
            When the waters finally went down, we saw what was left. Debris everywhere. Mud caked on everything we'd built.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="bg-brand-brown/5 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-brand-orange mb-6">
            <p class="font-hand text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed">
              We didn't post about it online. We didn't look for praise. We just did what folks in Braxton County do...
            </p>
          </blockquote>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed">
            FEMA denied us. <span class="text-brand-mud/70">Commercial business, they said.</span> Then came a theft — another ten thousand gone. No insurance to cover it.
          </p>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Page 6: Community Rises -->
      <section class="storybook-page mb-20">

        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-brand-brown text-center mb-8">
          Community Rises
        </h2>

        <div class="storybook-full-bleed -mx-6 md:-mx-12 mb-8">
          <img
            src="/story-sketch-community.jpg"
            alt="Pencil sketch showing church community members helping to rebuild after the flood"
            class="w-full shadow-2xl"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <p class="text-center font-hand text-brand-mud/50 mt-4 text-lg">Our church family from Tesla came to help</p>
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed text-center mb-6">
            We checked on our neighbors first. We prayed. And we dug out the mud — together.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed text-center mb-6">
            Even while digging out our own mess, Bryan was up on ladders fixing roofs for elderly neighbors and the church. That's just what you do.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed text-center mb-6">
            We kept the doors open because this community isn't just a market to us.
          </p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-display text-brand-brown text-center">
            It's home.
          </p>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Page 7: The New Beginning - Rebuild Sketch + Family Photo -->
      <section class="storybook-page mb-20">

        <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-brand-brown text-center mb-8">
          A New Beginning
        </h2>

        <div class="storybook-full-bleed -mx-6 md:-mx-12 mb-8">
          <img
            src="/story-sketch-rebuild.jpg"
            alt="Pencil sketch of the new WV Wild Outdoors building on the corner lot"
            class="w-full shadow-2xl"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed text-center mb-6">
            Then came the blessing we didn't expect — a federal contract. Enough to rebuild. Enough to start fresh.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed text-center mb-10">
            Rather than close the doors for good, we bought the <strong class="text-brand-brown">corner lot</strong> just down the road and moved WV Wild Outdoors there — keeping the shop close to the same neighbors, hunters, and families who had always depended on it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- The Family at the New Shop -->
        <div class="storybook-full-bleed -mx-6 md:-mx-12">
          <img
            src="/story-new-shop-family.jpg"
            alt="Kim and Bryan standing proudly at their new WV Wild Outdoors building"
            class="w-full rounded shadow-2xl"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <p class="text-center font-hand text-brand-mud/50 mt-4 text-lg">Kim & Bryan at the new corner lot — still standing</p>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Page 8: Today -->
      <section class="storybook-page mb-20 text-center">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-brand-mud leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
          Today, WV Wild Outdoors continues in that newer corner-lot location as a straightforward, local shop run by people who know the area they serve.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-brand-mud/70 max-w-xl mx-auto">
          Whether it's getting sighted in for buck season, stocking up on feed, or grabbing gear before a weekend in the woods — we're here to help.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- The Big Quote - Full Page -->
      <section class="storybook-page py-16 border-y-4 border-brand-orange/30 mb-20 text-center">
        <p class="font-hand text-3xl md:text-5xl text-brand-brown leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          "We own the building. We own every single thing in it. That's God."
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Final Page -->
      <footer class="text-center">
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-brand-mud/70 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10 italic leading-relaxed">
          "When things are rough, you still praise God Almighty. When a door closes, definitely look for the blessing — because it indeed will come."
        </p>
        <p class="font-display font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-sign-green mb-4">
          God is Indeed Good All the Time
        </p>
        <div class="h-1 w-24 bg-brand-orange mx-auto rounded-full mb-8"></div>
        <p class="font-hand text-brand-mud/50 text-xl">— Kim & Bryan Utt</p>
      </footer>

    </article>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Storybook page styling */
  .storybook-page {
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .storybook-spread {
    position: relative;
  }

  /* Image frame styling */
  .storybook-image img,
  .storybook-full-bleed img {
    border: 1px solid rgba(139, 90, 43, 0.1);
  }
</style>
